  "signature": "ed25519:5a324f2e55a3f17630e700f94626ef388bf3c6883860dd9c2a86c3361812482ce518685bf240b648f6077ee678b77cb2cc900cbf5219ad50b8682fa366ed0b0e",
  "hasCredibilityFactor": [
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Software quality assurance",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/sqa-level1-cpb",
      "rationale": "Commercial CFD solver (ANSYS Fluent 2023R2) with documented V&V pedigree and ISO 9001-certified release process. Solver regression test suite executed prior to study; all 847 benchmark cases passed. Software version control and audit trail maintained throughout the simulation campaign. Achieved Gradation 2 exceeds the MRL 2 requirement of Gradation 1."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/code-verification-level1-cpb",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to the incompressible Navier-Stokes solver confirming second-order spatial accuracy. Lid-driven cavity and backward-facing step benchmark cases reproduced to within 0.3% of published DNS data. Code verification activities documented in solver theory manual section 4.2 and internal verification report VR-2024-003."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-error-level2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Three-level structured mesh refinement study performed (coarse: 4.2M cells, medium: 12.1M cells, fine: 34.8M cells). Grid convergence index (GCI) computed per Roache (1998) methodology. GCI for hemolysis index QoI: 3.1% (medium-to-fine), confirming monotonic convergence. Richardson extrapolation applied; asymptotic range ratio = 1.02. Medium mesh selected for production runs with explicit GCI uncertainty bound reported. Exceeds MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-level2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Experimental test conditions documented including blood analog fluid properties (glycerol-water, 37°C, viscosity 3.5 mPa·s), pump rotational speed (2400–3600 RPM in 300 RPM increments), and flow rates (3–7 L/min). Temperature controlled to ±0.5°C. Inlet/outlet pressure measured with calibrated transducers (±0.5 mmHg). All five operating points bracket the clinical CPB envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-level2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Maximum relative error: 8.4% at 3 L/min / 3600 RPM; mean absolute relative error: 5.1%. Pressure-rise curve agreement within 4.2% across full operating range. Comparison methodology follows ASME V&V 20 with combined experimental and numerical uncertainty intervals reported. All simulation results fall within combined uncertainty bands."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-level2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) computed via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage model integrated along Lagrangian particle trajectories. These QoIs are directly mapped to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate). Secondary QoI (pump head and efficiency) provide mechanistic corroboration. QoI selection reviewed and approved by the clinical advisory panel."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-level2-cpb",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry — the same geometry used in the COU simulations. Operating conditions span the clinical CPB flow-speed envelope. Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water) properties matched to physiological blood viscosity at 37°C. Geometric fidelity confirmed by CMM measurement of test article (dimensional deviations < 0.05 mm from nominal CAD). Validation domain overlap with COU assessed as high."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-scopedout-cpb",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2, separate numerical solver error assessment beyond code verification and discretization error is not required per ASME V&V 40 Table 4. Iterative convergence monitored via residual norms (all below 1e-5) and mass imbalance (< 0.01%). Round-off error negligible for double-precision arithmetic at this Reynolds number regime. Scoped out with documented justification consistent with MRL 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-scopedout-cpb",
      "rationale": "Simulation workflow executed by experienced CFD engineers with > 5 years hemolysis modeling experience. Peer review of simulation setup conducted by independent analyst prior to production runs. Input deck version-controlled in Git repository (commit hash recorded in provenance). At MRL 2, formal use-error assessment beyond peer review not required; scoped out accordingly."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-scopedout-cpb",
      "rationale": "RANS k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on published benchmark studies for rotating blood pump geometries. Model form uncertainty addressed qualitatively through literature survey confirming SST performance for similar rotational Reynolds numbers (Re_rot ~ 4×10^4). At MRL 2, quantitative model form uncertainty propagation is not required; scoped out with documented literature basis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-scopedout-cpb",
      "rationale": "Boundary conditions derived from calibrated experimental measurements with documented uncertainty. Fluid properties sourced from NIST reference data and validated against in-house rheometry. Geometric inputs from CMM-verified CAD model. Sensitivity of NIH to ±5% variation in inlet velocity and fluid viscosity assessed via two additional simulation pairs; NIH variation < 2.8%. Formal UQ propagation scoped out at MRL 2; qualitative sensitivity documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-samples-na-cpb",
      "rationale": "Test samples factor pertains to variability across multiple physical test articles. This COU uses a single FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry as the reference; manufacturing variability assessment is addressed through the dimensional tolerance sensitivity study under Model Inputs. No population of test samples is relevant to this computational credibility assessment; factor designated not-applicable per ASME V&V 40 scoping guidance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "not-applicable",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/equivalency-inputs-na-cpb",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters factor applies when simulation inputs are derived from a different physical system than the COU device. In this assessment, boundary conditions are measured directly on the FDA generic pump geometry under CPB-representative conditions; no cross-system parameter mapping is required. Factor designated not-applicable; the validation and COU share identical geometry and operating fluid."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/cpb-hemolysis-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels for Model Risk Level 2. Discretization error (GCI 3.1%, asymptotic convergence confirmed) and software quality assurance (ISO 9001-certified solver with full regression testing) both exceed minimum requirements. Validation against experimental hemolysis data at five operating points yields mean absolute relative error of 5.1%, within combined uncertainty intervals at all points. The six scoped-out or not-applicable factors are appropriately justified per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for MRL 2. The relative hemolysis index RH = 0.83 (95th percentile including GCI uncertainty bound: 0.91) satisfies the RH < 1 acceptance criterion relative to the predicate device. The COU decision consequence is High and model influence is Medium, yielding MRL 2; the credibility evidence is commensurate with this risk level. The assessment team accepts the computational model as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device under the stated COU.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
